  "doc": "Steam Game Mode exposes Valve's 28de:11ff virtual output under either the canonical Steam Virtual Gamepad name or the SDL Xbox-compatible alias. Both names receive complete SDL2 autoconfig profiles and normalize to the same display identity. RetroArch selects SDL joypad index 0 with autodetection enabled; no name-based device reservation is generated. Autoconfiguration success and failure notifications are disabled while gameplay remains complete and the hotkey-enable button stays explicitly unbound. Semu's independent Start+Select watcher and held keyboard/radial actions own emulator control. Physical Steam Game Mode UI proof remains open and cannot be inferred from this declaration."
